# AI / Agent Standards

Details: `docs/ai-architecture.md`, Constitution §5, §21, §22, §23.

- **Deterministic-first.** Classify each unit as Deterministic / LLM Step / true Agent; pick the least autonomous that works.
- **Structured I/O only** — typed input, schema-validated output. Never pass free text a downstream must parse.
- **Grounding is mandatory.** No skills/experience not in the source Profile version. Zero-fabrication is a hard eval gate.
- **No external-write tools exist.** No tool submits applications or messages third parties. Email/calendar are user-facing only.
- **Human-in-the-loop is structural:** externally-bound/representational artifacts require a `ReviewTask` + approval before leaving the platform. The Supervisor cannot bypass it and holds no external-write tools.
- **State is typed, namespaced, reference-based.** Pass IDs/summaries, not payloads/transcripts/embeddings.
- **Bounded loops** (capped retries, self-critique iterations, plan depth). Checkpoint + trace every Agent Run (LangSmith + `AgentRun`, one `traceId`).
- **All LLM access behind the `LLMProvider` port.** No hardcoded model names — select via the routing config. No LLM on the request path.
- **Prompts live in `agents/prompts/`, versioned** — never inline. Each prompt has eval cases + a guardrail.
- **Untrusted/ingested text can never escalate tool permissions or write long-term memory.** Memory is consent-scoped and decaying.
